"use strict";(self.webpackChunkmonochord_web=self.webpackChunkmonochord_web||[]).push([[8130],{7735:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"microton-vst-release","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/microton-vst-release","source":"@site/blog/2025-10-11-microtonvst-release.md","title":"MicrotonVST for Windows and macOS","description":"We\u2019re excited to announce the release of MicrotonVST for Windows and macOS!","date":"2025-10-11T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.52,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Euclidean Instruments","title":"Development team","url":"https://euclidean-instruments.com","imageURL":"img/littlelogo.png","key":"euclid"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"microton-vst-release","title":"MicrotonVST for Windows and macOS","authors":["euclid"]},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"PolySampler launch!","permalink":"/blog/polysampler-launch"}},"content":"We\u2019re excited to announce the release of MicrotonVST for Windows and macOS!\\n\\nMicrotonVST features all of the sonic possibilities of the original Microton along with the convenience of the VST3 format. Now Windows and Mac users can bring true microtonal music to any DAW or software that supports the VST3 standard.\\n\\nThe MicrotonVST also includes a standalone synth application for use outside of DAW software, so you can instantly turn your desktop into a self-contained microtonal synth.\\n\\nMicrotonVST is DRM-free and includes all future updates and patches. Best of all, it\u2019s currently available at the introductory price of $5.\\n\\n[Get MicrotonVST on Gumroad here!](https://euclideaninstruments.gumroad.com/l/microtonvst)"},{"id":"polysampler-launch","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/polysampler-launch","source":"@site/blog/2025-03-27 polysampler-launch/polysampler-launch.md","title":"PolySampler launch!","description":"We\'re proud to announce the release of the PolySampler for iPad and iPhone.","date":"2025-03-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.39,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Euclidean Instruments","title":"Development team","url":"https://euclidean-instruments.com","imageURL":"img/littlelogo.png","key":"euclid"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"polysampler-launch","title":"PolySampler launch!","authors":["euclid"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"MicrotonVST for Windows and macOS","permalink":"/blog/microton-vst-release"},"nextItem":{"title":"An Introduction to the Microton tuning system","permalink":"/blog/an-introduction-to-the-microton-tuning-system"}},"content":"We\'re proud to announce the release of the PolySampler for iPad and iPhone.\\n\\n[![PolySampler on the Apple App Store](./polysampler_launch.png)](https://apple.co/4j9ChcO)\\n\\nPolySampler gives you the ability to craft unique sounds anywhere you go using your iPhone or iPad. Sixteen individual tracks, each with time-stretching, FX loop, and more. Load samples from your device or use your built-in microphone to use anything as your sound source. Save your favorite samples for use anytime. PolySampler is the most convenient sampler ever built."},{"id":"an-introduction-to-the-microton-tuning-system","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/an-introduction-to-the-microton-tuning-system","source":"@site/blog/2024-11-02-tuning-intro/2024-11-02-tuning-intro.md","title":"An Introduction to the Microton tuning system","description":"Let\'s have some fun with the Microton\'s tuning system.","date":"2024-11-02T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":1.46,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Euclidean Instruments","title":"Development team","url":"https://euclidean-instruments.com","imageURL":"img/littlelogo.png","key":"euclid"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"an-introduction-to-the-microton-tuning-system","title":"An Introduction to the Microton tuning system","authors":["euclid"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"PolySampler launch!","permalink":"/blog/polysampler-launch"},"nextItem":{"title":"Microton and Microton FM available on the Apple App Store","permalink":"/blog/release-day"}},"content":"Let\'s have some fun with the Microton\'s tuning system.\\n\\n![Default tuning](./default.png)\\n\\nThe Microton defaults to 12-tone equal temperament (or 12-TET for short) at A440. (Each element\'s frequency is exactly 100 cents from the previous element, using A4 = 400hz as a starting point.) When we click on each element on the monochord, we can see its properties in the Element Editor.\\n\\n\x3c!--truncate--\x3e\\n\\n![Element Editor](./element_editor.png)\\n\\nExperimenting with alternate standards is simple; we select the root element and input a different frequency. Here, as a tribute to Leonard Bernstein, we retune to A442:\\n\\n![A442](./a442.png)\\n\\nThe monochord updates all of the other elements (and, by extension, the MIDI map) using the new tuning standard.\\n\\nWhat if we want to do something weird, like C4 = 500hz? Retune the root to 500hz, and input \'C4\' in the MIDI transpose field:\\n\\n![C500](./c500.png)\\n\\nWe can also modify the elements directly to create our own tuning systems. One way is to simply click/touch and element and drag across the monochord:\\n\\n![Element drag gif](./element_gif.gif)\\n\\nFor more precision we\'ll turn back to the Element Editor. First, let\'s load the Just 5-Limit Augmented 4 tuning. To transform this tuning into its closely related Just 5-Limit Diminished 5 intonation, we modify the ratio of the tritone to 45/32.\\n\\n![Aug to dim](./aug_to_dim.gif)\\n\\nFinally, we can use the tuning system to quickly generate tuning templates to experiment with by using the \'Generate Equaltone Tuning\' option. Here, we generate a quarter-tone tuning:\\n\\n![Quarter-tone](./quartertone.gif)\\n\\nAnd another example, where we generate a 9-tone equal tone tuning, then remove the second and sixth elements, which is the basis for the Microton\'s preset version of the Javanese Pelog tuning:\\n\\n\\\\![Pelog](./pelog.gif)\\n\\nSimple to learn, endless potential. Microton gives you the tools to speak any musical language - or create your own."},{"id":"release-day","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/release-day","source":"@site/blog/2024-11-01-release-day/2024-11-01-release-day.md","title":"Microton and Microton FM available on the Apple App Store","description":"Microton and Microton FM are officially available for purchase for desktop and iOS!","date":"2024-11-01T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.11,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Euclidean Instruments","title":"Development team","url":"https://euclidean-instruments.com","imageURL":"img/littlelogo.png","key":"euclid"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"release-day","title":"Microton and Microton FM available on the Apple App Store","authors":["euclid"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"An Introduction to the Microton tuning system","permalink":"/blog/an-introduction-to-the-microton-tuning-system"},"nextItem":{"title":"Hello World!","permalink":"/blog/hello-world"}},"content":"Microton and Microton FM are officially available for purchase for desktop and iOS!\\n\\n[![Microton app store link](./appstore.png)](https://apple.co/3A1akCW)\\n\\n[![Microton FM app store link](./appstoreFM.png)](https://apple.co/3YKix8a)"},{"id":"hello-world","metadata":{"permalink":"/blog/hello-world","source":"@site/blog/2024-10-15-first-blog-post.md","title":"Hello World!","description":"Microton launches October 2024!","date":"2024-10-15T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[],"readingTime":0.085,"hasTruncateMarker":false,"authors":[{"name":"Euclidean Instruments","title":"Development team","url":"https://euclidean-instruments.com","imageURL":"img/littlelogo.png","key":"euclid"}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"hello-world","title":"Hello World!","authors":["euclid"]},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Microton and Microton FM available on the Apple App Store","permalink":"/blog/release-day"}},"content":"Microton launches October 2024!\\n\\nWe\'ll be posting news, tutorials, videos, and other fun stuff here. Stay tuned!"}]}}')}}]);